cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.DL 

This paper focuses on analyzing the behavior and position of users in the Twitter network, which falls under the category of social media analysis. The paper proposes a method to identify the community roles of social capitalists, which involves network analysis and community detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Additionally, the paper also involves unsupervised role identification, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and the use of an existing tool to detect social capitalists, which involves deep learning (cs.DL).
